body:
First, examine the following code, and its resulting error message:
```Rust
fn main() {
    let v64: u64 = 64;
    let v32: u32 = 32;
    
    unsafe {
        println!("{}", mem::transmute::<u32, u64>(v32));
    }
}
```
```
error[E0512]: transmute called with differently sized types: u32 (32 bits) to u64 (64 bits)
  --> <anon>:44:24
   |
 6 |         println!("{}", mem::transmute::<u32, u64>(v32));
   |                        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ transmuting between 32 bits and 64 bits
```
Specifically, notice that the size of each type is listed in the error message:  "u32 (**32 bits**) to u64 (**64 bits**)".

Now, examine this code and its resulting error message:
```Rust
use std::mem;

trait HasAddress {
    fn get_address(&self) -> *const u32 {
        unsafe { mem::transmute::<&Self, *const u32>(self) }
    }
}

fn main() { }
```
```
error[E0512]: transmute called with differently sized types: &Self (pointer to Self) to *const u32 (64 bits)
 --> <anon>:5:18
  |
5 |         unsafe { mem::transmute::<&Self, *const u32>(self) }
  |                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ transmuting between pointer to Self and 64 bits
```

I'm assuming two issues here:

1. In the error message for the last example, the size for `&Self` is printed as "(pointer to Self)" instead of the actual numeric size as was printed in the first example.
2. `&Self` and `*const u32` are both addresses, so I'm assuming they should transmute fine without error.
